Probiotics at this point are everywhere üëÄ
.
You will find an array of probiotics in both supplement and food form, but not all probiotics are the same.
.
Here is a great and detailed post by my friend @bernadette.abraham .
First things first. When a new client tells me they take probiotics, it‚Äôs the same thing as telling me they eat food.ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
.
Not very helpful or specific is it? So let‚Äôs learn some basic facts.ü§ì
.
In nutrition, we broadly categorize food into nutrients: protein, carbs and fats.
.
With probiotics, scientists have also classified them into three categories: genus, species and strains.üíÅ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
.
üëâüèªGenus refers to the family of probiotic ‚Äì for example, canine.
.
üëâüèªSpecies refers to the group ‚Äì i.e. dogs.
.
üëâüèªAnd strains are the subtypes ‚Äì i.e. dog breeds.
.
The genus can be ‚Äútransient‚Äù meaning you poop it out after a few days üò≤ or ‚Äúnative‚Äù - meaning it colonizes in the gut in much larger numbers than transient bacteria, and comes from air, water, soil and the vaginal birth canal during birth.üí™üèº
.
We need both types.
.
The majority of probiotic supplements available over the counter are formulated with ‚Äútransient‚Äù genera called Lactobacillus and Bifidobacterium (see infograph for specific benefits), which are also abundantly found in fermented or cultured foods (and not to mention are much more diverse).üå±
.
Eating fermented foods and/or taking broad-spectrum probiotics regularly helps keep a steady supply of beneficial bacteria in the gut.üôåüèª
.
But just like diets, there‚Äôs no one-size-fits-all probiotic. Different circumstances call for different genus, species and strains.üôÉ
.
‚ö†Ô∏èFor instance, those with microbial overgrowths (i.e. SIBO) should avoid probiotic formulations containing pre-biotics (i.e. food for probiotics) like FOS or inulin. It‚Äôs like adding fuel to fire!üî•
.
‚ö†Ô∏èThose with constipation should choose probiotics with higher concentrations of Bifidobacterium than Lactobacillus.
.
‚ö†Ô∏èThose with yeast sensitivity should avoid taking S. Boulardii ‚Äì even though it‚Äôs a beneficial type of yeast.
.
As you can see, different strands for different people üòä
.
#probiotic #probiotics #prebiotics #prebiotic #guthealth #healthygut

Yes, the food you eat even affects your sex life üòâüôÉ
.
I want everyone to know how hard it is to wink in a picture and not come off creepy as can be ü§£
.
Soooo.. When it comes to the topic of having better sex, there are 2 parts that come into play.
.
Part 1 is trying to increase your libido or sex drive in some way.
.
Part 2 is increasing blood flow to both the female and male organs, similar to what Viagra would do for a man. Viagra doesn‚Äôt actually increase sex drive, it gives you an erection, so it is all performance based, not actually hormone based.
.
In this case, foods would fall into 1 of these 2 categories.
.
Oysters are great for providing zinc, which is essential for both a female‚Äôs and male‚Äôs libido. They also contain D-aspartic acid which is a precursor to testosterone and has been shown to possibly increase sperm production in men.
.
Watermelon¬†is the richest known dietary source of the amino acid¬†citrulline. L-citrulline supports the body in optimizing blood flow when it converts to L-arginine and then to nitric oxide.
.
Dark chocolate contains specific flavonoids that help to improve¬†blood flow. It also increases serotonin and dopamine levels in the brain, making us happy and then puts us in the 'mood‚Äô. Lastly dark chocolate also contains phenylethylamine, a compound that has been shown to produce feelings of euphoria.
.
Arugula contains high amounts of dietary nitrates. Nitrates will convert into nitric oxide in the body, thus vastly improving blood flow.
.
Garlic contains allicin, a compound thought to increase blood flow to the sexual organs. Some experts believe that garlic is also a very powerful aphrodisiac.
.
Cloves are a spice that can help your sex life in a few ways. They have one of the best aromatherapy effects on sexual behavior. Cloves also contain eugenol which can boost your cardiovascular system.
.
Overall, these are just some foods you can include in your diet to help your sex life in multiple ways.
.

What is the diet that we should be eating? Should we include meat? Or should it be 100% plant based? ü§îüí≠ .

While I do enjoy a good debate filled with science, I also like to ground my thoughts and put myself in the shoes üëû of the average person, just trying to eat‚Ä¶ BETTER.

When you are eating a S.A.D. diet as most of the country does, EITHER an omnivore whole food based diet with tons of plants and some meat OR a fully vegan diet‚Ä¶. are both giant steps forward!
.
This picture was taken at a food store close to me. What do you notice? Tons of cereal choices, then you swipe and you see whole aisles filled with conventional cereal, cookies, granola bars and candy. There are literally 30+ different boxes of cereal and even 15 flavors of Oreos‚Ä¶ These are only on the shelf because someone is buying them! ü§¶üèº‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è
.
My point, is that this is the bigger picture. Our stores are still 90% filled with food like products and the average person is over eating calories and under eating micronutrients of all kinds; fiber, pre and probiotics, protein, healthy fats and more. So, eating whole foods with a lot of plants is still really where most people need to strive to be‚Ä¶. Whether or not they have meat on their plate.

So, while I think the next few years will be filled with endless debates on this topic, I just want to remind everyone to take a step back and look at the entire picture!

Here are 6 foods that can help with your overall thyroid health!

Brazil Nuts ü•ú: The thyroid has the highest selenium content of any organ, and studies suggest that selenium deficiencies may be a primary cause of thyroid disorders. Selenium helps the conversion of thyroid hormones T3-T4 and 1-2 brazil nuts gives you a good amount of selenium.

Apples üçé: Apples are rich in pectins, a gelatinous fiber that helps clear the body of heavy metals, especially mercury, which has been associated with thyroid disorders.
.
Pumpkin Seeds üéÉ: Zinc is critical for the synthesis of thyroid hormones, and deficiencies can lead to hypothyroidism.
.
Kelp üå±: The thyroid requires iodine, a trace mineral, to synthesize sufficient amounts of thyroid hormones, and studies show that even mild iodine deficiencies can lead to thyroid problems.
.
Broccoli Sprouts ü•¶: Sulforaphane improves detoxification enzymes in the body. Cruciferous veggies as a whole contain phytochemicals and help your hormones function daily.
